CatDescriptText: image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 16, 1960, pg. B7, reads: "D.I.'s Guest - Cute Loretta Wiley of Tougaloo College, Miss., right, was the guest of the smart D.I. Club in Pittsburgh last Sunday night when the annual benefit fashion show-dancing party was given to benefit the march of Dimes. Center is Mrs. Gay DeHall, president of the energetic club group, and seated left, is her daughter Diane, a Michigan State College student. - Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Diane DeHall, Gay Dehall wearing satin dress with imprinted vine pattern, and Loretta Wiley, gathered in interior of the New Arena Supper Club for D. I. Club National Foundation benefit
